272
00:10:06,910 --> 00:10:08,450
We'll need
a new disguise.

273
00:10:08,630 --> 00:10:12,070
[ Pitter! ]

274
00:10:12,190 --> 00:10:13,890
[ Chimes play ]

275
00:10:19,190 --> 00:10:21,270
She didn't see you
at the sweet shop, did she?

276
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:22,670
I don't think so.

277
00:10:22,950 --> 00:10:25,470
Oh, good. I'd hate for her
to ruin everything.

278
00:10:25,830 --> 00:10:26,770
Me too.

279
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:28,210
[ Sloop! Plop! ]

280
00:10:30,230 --> 00:10:30,750
[ Creak! ]

281
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:39,990
[ Creak! ]

282
00:10:40,130 --> 00:10:40,830
[ Boing! ]

283
00:10:42,010 --> 00:10:42,410
[ Pop! ]

284
00:10:42,770 --> 00:10:43,370
[ Squeaks ]

285
00:10:43,790 --> 00:10:44,930
[ Sneezes ]

286
00:10:47,070 --> 00:10:47,530
[ Sloop! ]

287
00:10:50,930 --> 00:10:51,570
[ Squeak! ]

288
00:10:53,290 --> 00:10:54,430
Rarity:
have you seen her?

289
00:10:54,530 --> 00:10:55,490
Fluttershy:
not since this morning.

290
00:10:55,790 --> 00:10:56,750
Me neither.

291
00:10:57,010 --> 00:10:58,750
Can you believe she was
planning on throwing

292
00:10:58,810 --> 00:11:00,410
An after-Birthday party
today?

293
00:11:00,610 --> 00:11:02,810
I'm just glad I was able
to come up with an excuse

294
00:11:02,890 --> 00:11:03,830
For why I couldn't
be there.

295
00:11:04,210 --> 00:11:07,090
Me too. This is obviously
going to be so much better.

296
00:11:07,810 --> 00:11:08,770
As long as we keep her

297
00:11:08,830 --> 00:11:10,190
From finding out about it,
it will.

298
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:13,650
See you later.

299
00:11:17,570 --> 00:11:18,630
[ Boing! Boing! Boing! ]

300
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:19,310
[ Thump! ]
Oh!

301
00:11:19,590 --> 00:11:20,430
[ Boing! Boing! Boing! Boing! ]

302
00:11:20,490 --> 00:11:21,050
Oh!

303
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:23,410
[ Gasps ]

304
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:24,490
[ Sloop! ]

305
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:25,630
Aah!

306
00:11:26,010 --> 00:11:26,970
[ Zoom! ]

307
00:11:28,210 --> 00:11:30,750
I thought everypony
loved my parties.

308
00:11:31,670 --> 00:11:32,530
Hi, Pinkie Pie.

309
00:11:32,850 --> 00:11:33,810
[ Twang! ]

310
00:11:34,410 --> 00:11:35,410
Uh-Oh!
[ Whoosh! ]

311
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:37,590
Rainbow Dash, wait!

312
00:11:38,170 --> 00:11:39,090
[ Whoosh! ]

313
00:11:39,930 --> 00:11:41,430
[ Whoosh! ]

314
00:11:43,390 --> 00:11:43,850
Whew!

315
00:11:43,890 --> 00:11:44,830
Where are you going?!
Aah!

316
00:11:44,950 --> 00:11:45,490
[ Whoosh! ]

317
00:11:47,430 --> 00:11:48,230
[ Whoosh! ]

318
00:11:48,530 --> 00:11:49,050
[ Sloop! ]

319
00:11:49,650 --> 00:11:50,130
[ Clang! ]

320
00:11:52,030 --> 00:11:52,750
[ Creak! ]

321
00:11:54,170 --> 00:11:55,190
What's the real reason

322
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:57,130
You didn't want
to come to Gummy's party?!

323
00:11:57,770 --> 00:11:58,430
[ Zip! ]

324
00:11:59,630 --> 00:12:03,150
[ Whoosh! ]

325
00:12:04,770 --> 00:12:05,370
[ Grunts ]

326
00:12:09,490 --> 00:12:11,170
What's in that bag?!

327
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:12,090
[ Whoosh! ]

328
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:13,130
[ Zip! ]

329
00:12:15,110 --> 00:12:16,370
[ Whoosh! Whoosh! ]

330
00:12:16,530 --> 00:12:17,450
[ Zip! Whoosh! ]

331
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:19,450
Applejack, we have a problem!

332
00:12:21,950 --> 00:12:22,950
[ Gasps ]

333
00:12:23,010 --> 00:12:23,890
[ Slam! ]

334
00:12:24,650 --> 00:12:26,070
[ Conk! Conk! Conk!
Conk! Conk! Conk! ]

335
00:12:26,730 --> 00:12:28,830
I know you're in there!

336
00:12:30,450 --> 00:12:31,870
Oh, uh, howdy, partner.

337
00:12:32,370 --> 00:12:34,930
Mind if I take a look
inside the barn?

338
00:12:36,070 --> 00:12:36,450
No.

339
00:12:36,510 --> 00:12:37,410
Uh, I mean yes.

340
00:12:37,510 --> 00:12:38,810
I mean
you can't come in here.

341
00:12:39,190 --> 00:12:40,530
Rainbow Dash
just went in there.

342
00:12:40,810 --> 00:12:44,150
Oh, well, she was just bringing
in some...supplies, yep.

343
00:12:44,370 --> 00:12:46,210
Supplies
for the r-Renovation.

344
00:12:46,290 --> 00:12:48,310
Fixing up the whole thing,
top to bottom.

345
00:12:48,570 --> 00:12:51,610
Uh, lots of construction
going on in there right now!

346
00:12:51,830 --> 00:12:53,910
You heard her!
Construction!

347
00:12:54,430 --> 00:12:58,510
[ Ponies imitating animals ]

348
00:12:59,590 --> 00:13:01,570
[ Sloop! ]

349
00:13:02,950 --> 00:13:03,450
[ Whip! ]

350
00:13:04,070 --> 00:13:06,510
[ Creak! Creak! Creak! Creak! ]

351
00:13:08,470 --> 00:13:09,170
[ Creak! ]

352
00:13:09,290 --> 00:13:10,550
[ Creak! Creak! Creak! ]

353
00:13:10,590 --> 00:13:11,390
[ Smack! ]

354
00:13:12,070 --> 00:13:12,730
[ Tinkle! ]

355
00:13:12,930 --> 00:13:14,490
Yep, construction.

356
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:16,110
That's my story,
and I'm sticking to it.

357
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:16,530
[ Chuckles ]

358
00:13:20,670 --> 00:13:21,290
[ Gulp! ]

359
00:13:28,510 --> 00:13:30,850
Okie-Dokie-Lokie.

360
00:13:31,750 --> 00:13:32,130
[ Sighs ]

361
00:13:32,230 --> 00:13:32,970
[ Whip! ]

362
00:13:35,770 --> 00:13:36,530
[ Sighs ]

363
00:13:37,510 --> 00:13:38,590
[ All sigh ]

364
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:42,430
Secrets and lies.

365
00:13:42,570 --> 00:13:44,730
It's all secrets and lies
with those ponies.

366
00:13:44,950 --> 00:13:46,570
They're up to something, Gummy,

367
00:13:46,730 --> 00:13:48,410
Something they don't want me
to know about.

368
00:13:48,950 --> 00:13:51,010
[ Boing! ]
Well, I'm gonna know
about it!

369
00:13:51,110 --> 00:13:52,770
I'm gonna know about it
big time!

370
00:13:52,930 --> 00:13:55,970
And I know just who's
gonna tell me all about it --

371
00:13:56,070 --> 00:13:58,270
Tell me all about it
big time!

372
00:13:59,730 --> 00:14:01,810
Wow! Nice spread.

373
00:14:03,130 --> 00:14:04,730
It's all yours, Spike.

374
00:14:05,830 --> 00:14:06,730
[ Clink! ]

375
00:14:06,790 --> 00:14:07,290
[ Squeak! ]

376
00:14:07,430 --> 00:14:09,090
[ Clank! Clank! ]

377
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:11,650
All you have to do
is talk.

378
00:14:13,530 --> 00:14:15,150
That's it?
Oh, you got it.

379
00:14:15,350 --> 00:14:17,250
Okay. Uh, beautiful weather
we're having, eh?

380
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:19,490
I love a sunny spring day.
Don't you?

381
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:22,150
The birds chirping,
the flowers blooming.

382
00:14:22,210 --> 00:14:24,710
No, no, no.
Talk about our friends.

383
00:14:25,890 --> 00:14:27,450
Oh, okay.
Let's see.

384
00:14:27,570 --> 00:14:29,650
There's Twilight Sparkle.
She's the unicorn.

385
00:14:29,810 --> 00:14:31,750
Good with magic,
real brainiac.

386
00:14:31,910 --> 00:14:34,330
And then you got Rarity --
Total knockout.

387
00:14:34,550 --> 00:14:36,170
Twilight seems to think
I don't have a chance with her,

388
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,310
But, eh,
what does she know?

389
00:14:37,590 --> 00:14:37,930
Let's see.

390
00:14:37,970 --> 00:14:40,290
There's -- There's Fluttershy,
a pegasus afraid of heights.

391
00:14:40,390 --> 00:14:42,410
Huh!
What's up with that?
Ugh! No!

392
00:14:42,470 --> 00:14:43,710
You're not
understanding me!

393
00:14:43,930 --> 00:14:45,570
I want you to confess!

394
00:14:45,870 --> 00:14:48,010
Confess?
Confess!

395
00:14:51,110 --> 00:14:52,850
I'm the one who spilled juice
all over Twilight's copy

396
00:14:52,930 --> 00:14:54,650
Of "magical mysteries
and practical potions"!

397
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:55,030
[ Squeak! ]

398
00:14:55,890 --> 00:14:56,690
And?

399
00:14:57,490 --> 00:14:58,530
And I'm the one who used up

400
00:14:58,570 --> 00:14:59,990
All the hot water
in Ponyville yesterday

401
00:15:00,030 --> 00:15:01,350
When I took
a seven-Hour bubble bath!

402
00:15:01,390 --> 00:15:01,690
[ Squeak! ]

403
00:15:02,170 --> 00:15:03,310
And?

404
00:15:04,450 --> 00:15:07,130
And sometimes, when no one's
around, I do this.

405
00:15:07,170 --> 00:15:07,710
[ Creak! Whip! ]

406
00:15:08,090 --> 00:15:10,310
[ Creak! ]
Lookin' good, Spike!

407
00:15:10,370 --> 00:15:11,870
Lookin' real good!

408
00:15:13,590 --> 00:15:14,530
[ Tink! Tink! ]

409
00:15:14,930 --> 00:15:15,550
[ Rattle! ]

410
00:15:15,610 --> 00:15:17,870
No, no, no, no!

411
00:15:18,790 --> 00:15:20,390
W-What do you want
to hear?

412
00:15:20,430 --> 00:15:22,290
Tell me what you want me to say,
and I'll say it!

413
00:15:22,510 --> 00:15:24,790
Tell me that my friends are
lying to me and avoiding me

414
00:15:24,870 --> 00:15:25,910
Because they don't
like my parties

415
00:15:25,970 --> 00:15:27,970
And they don't want to
be my friends anymore!

416
00:15:28,110 --> 00:15:30,470
[ Panting ]

417
00:15:30,850 --> 00:15:32,330
Your friends are all lying
to you and avoiding you

418
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:33,230
'Cause they don't
like your parties

419
00:15:33,290 --> 00:15:34,550
And they don't want to
be your friends anymore!

420
00:15:34,610 --> 00:15:36,850
Aha! I knew it!

421
00:15:37,530 --> 00:15:38,650
[ Creak! ]

422
00:15:38,710 --> 00:15:40,170
[ Pop! Gust! ]

423
00:15:41,590 --> 00:15:42,310
Oh, no!

424
00:15:42,570 --> 00:15:43,870
My friends don't
like my parties,

425
00:15:43,930 --> 00:15:45,910
And they don't want to
be me friends anymore.

426
00:15:48,850 --> 00:15:50,830
[ Click ]
uh, so...

427
00:15:51,930 --> 00:15:52,510
aw!

428
00:15:52,610 --> 00:15:53,710
[ Chomp! ]
Mm-Mmm!

429
00:15:53,770 --> 00:15:56,350
Mm-Mmm!
[ Sighs ]

430
00:15:58,370 --> 00:16:00,250
Thank you all
so much for coming.

431
00:16:00,310 --> 00:16:01,890
It means so much to Gummy.

432
00:16:02,210 --> 00:16:02,910
[ Chatters ]

433
00:16:03,530 --> 00:16:05,150
[ Deep voice ]
could I have some more punch?

434
00:16:05,650 --> 00:16:07,970
[ Normal voice ]
well, of course you can have
some more punch, Mr. Turnip.

435
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:08,970
[ Zip! ]

436
00:16:09,470 --> 00:16:10,170
[ Boing! ]

437
00:16:12,150 --> 00:16:13,870
[ Deep voice ]
this is one great party!

438
00:16:14,090 --> 00:16:15,950
You've really outdone yourself!

439
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:17,790
[ Normal voice ]
why, thank you, Rocky.

440
00:16:18,650 --> 00:16:21,350
[ Deep voice ] I'm having
a delightful time, as well.

441
00:16:21,810 --> 00:16:23,730
[ Normal voice ]
I'm so glad, sir Lints-A-Lot.

442
00:16:23,810 --> 00:16:24,470
[ Boing! ]

443
00:16:25,070 --> 00:16:28,230
[ High-Pitched voice ]
might I trouble you for
another slice of cake?

444
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:30,650
[ Normal voice ] anything
for you, Madame le Flour.

445
00:16:32,210 --> 00:16:34,950
[ Deep voice ] I'm just glad
none of them ponies showed up.

446
00:16:35,930 --> 00:16:38,130
[ Sloop! ]
[ Normal voice ]
oh, they're not so bad.

447
00:16:38,310 --> 00:16:38,770
[ Plop! Plop! ]

448
00:16:38,970 --> 00:16:41,070
[ Slump! ]

449
00:16:42,090 --> 00:16:44,130
Not so bad? Please.

450
00:16:44,530 --> 00:16:46,190
They're a bunch of losers.

451
00:16:47,990 --> 00:16:49,030
Oh, come on, now.

452
00:16:49,390 --> 00:16:51,890
"Losers" might be a little
strong, don't you think?

453
00:16:52,070 --> 00:16:53,970
After the way
they treated you?

454
00:16:54,110 --> 00:16:56,790
I say "losers"
isn't strong enough.

455
00:16:57,430 --> 00:16:59,150
Well, it was pretty rude.

456
00:16:59,890 --> 00:17:03,890
Pretty rude?
It was downright despicable!

457
00:17:04,550 --> 00:17:05,550
It was, wasn't it?

458
00:17:06,310 --> 00:17:09,590
If I were you, I wouldn't
speak to them ever again.

459
00:17:10,070 --> 00:17:10,990
You know what?

460
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:12,930
I'm not gonna speak to them
ever again,

461
00:17:13,050 --> 00:17:14,690
And I'm not gonna invite them
to another party

462
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:15,630
As long as I live!

463
00:17:15,950 --> 00:17:17,830
They don't deserve to be
invited to my parties!

464
00:17:17,890 --> 00:17:18,430
[ Screech! ]

465
00:17:18,770 --> 00:17:20,910
Not after the way
they've been acting.

466
00:17:21,030 --> 00:17:22,950
Despicable!
Bunch of losers!

467
00:17:22,990 --> 00:17:24,290
[ High-Pitched voice ]
yes, that's right!

468
00:17:24,590 --> 00:17:25,630
[ Deep voice ]
well done.

469
00:17:26,150 --> 00:17:27,990
Yeah, you show them!
[ Knock on door ]

470
00:17:28,070 --> 00:17:29,450
[ Twang! ]
Who could that be?

471
00:17:31,130 --> 00:17:32,230
Hey there, Pinkie Pie.

472
00:17:32,770 --> 00:17:34,570
Sorry I was in
such a rush earlier.

473
00:17:34,670 --> 00:17:36,670
Had someplace to be and couldn't
slow down and say hello.

474
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:38,070
You know how it goes.

475
00:17:38,450 --> 00:17:40,690
I know how it goes,
all right.

476
00:17:41,110 --> 00:17:41,930
Yeah.

477
00:17:42,130 --> 00:17:44,690
So, why don't you come with me
over to sweet apple acres?

478
00:17:44,990 --> 00:17:48,030
No, thanks. I'm spending time
with my real friends.

479
00:17:48,430 --> 00:17:50,110
Isn't that right,
Madame le Flour?

480
00:17:50,390 --> 00:17:52,610
[ High-Pitched voice ]
oui! That is correct, madame.

481
00:17:53,610 --> 00:17:55,030
Uh, Pinkie Pie?

482
00:17:55,250 --> 00:17:57,050
[ Normal voice ]
another slice of cake,
sir Lints-A-Lot?

483
00:17:57,270 --> 00:17:58,490
[ Deep voice ]
I'd love one.

484
00:17:59,050 --> 00:18:00,270
All righty.

485
00:18:00,710 --> 00:18:03,010
What do you say we get on
out of creepy town

486
00:18:03,090 --> 00:18:04,190
And head over
to Applejack's --

487
00:18:04,330 --> 00:18:05,890
She's not
going anywhere.

488
00:18:06,070 --> 00:18:07,410
[ Normal voice ]
I most certainly am not.

489
00:18:07,590 --> 00:18:10,270
I'm having a wonderful time
right here.
[ Zip! ]

490
00:18:10,610 --> 00:18:12,350
You should really
just come with me.

491
00:18:12,430 --> 00:18:13,730
[ Sloop! ]
[ Deep voice ]
you heard the lady!

492
00:18:13,790 --> 00:18:15,510
She ain't goin' nowheres,
chump!

493
00:18:16,190 --> 00:18:18,270
Who you callin'
a chump, chump?

494
00:18:20,050 --> 00:18:20,510
[ Sighs ]

495
00:18:20,750 --> 00:18:21,470
That's it.
Party's over.

496
00:18:21,570 --> 00:18:23,970
Come on, Pinkie Pie.
No!

497
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:27,030
Pinkie Pie, let's go!
I said no!

498
00:18:27,150 --> 00:18:27,530
[ Squeak! ]

499
00:18:27,670 --> 00:18:32,390
[ Creak! ]
You...have to...
come with...me!

500
00:18:32,510 --> 00:18:34,710
No...i...don't!

501
00:18:34,810 --> 00:18:35,070
[ Clang! ]

502
00:18:37,170 --> 00:18:38,150
[ Zip! Crash! ]

503
00:18:40,910 --> 00:18:42,250
Oh, you want to do this
the hard way?

504
00:18:42,490 --> 00:18:43,930
We'll do this
the hard way!

505
00:18:44,830 --> 00:18:49,930
[ Grunting ]

506
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:51,510
[ Panting ]

507
00:18:51,610 --> 00:18:53,310
We're...here.

508
00:18:55,550 --> 00:18:57,110
Surprise!
Surprise!
Surprise!
Surprise!

509
00:19:05,930 --> 00:19:08,050
I really thought
she'd be more excited.

510
00:19:08,850 --> 00:19:11,070
Excited?! Excited?!

511
00:19:11,390 --> 00:19:14,370
Why would I be excited to attend
my own farewell party?!

512
00:19:15,070 --> 00:19:16,370
Farewell party?

513
00:19:16,690 --> 00:19:17,250
Yes!

514
00:19:17,330 --> 00:19:18,430
You don't like me anymore,

515
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:19,910
So you decided to kick me
out of the group

516
00:19:19,990 --> 00:19:21,930
And throw a great big party
to celebrate,

517
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,950
A-Farewell-To-Pinkie Pie
party!

518
00:19:25,990 --> 00:19:27,510
Why in the world
would you think

519
00:19:27,610 --> 00:19:29,090
We didn't like you anymore,
sugar cube?

520
00:19:29,270 --> 00:19:30,230
Why?

521
00:19:30,750 --> 00:19:31,890
Why?!

522
00:19:32,310 --> 00:19:33,870
Why?!
Oh!

523
00:19:34,210 --> 00:19:37,170
Because you've been lying to me
and avoiding me all day!

524
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:38,750
That's why!

525
00:19:39,730 --> 00:19:43,450
Uh, yeah, because we wanted
your party to be a surprise.

526
00:19:44,330 --> 00:19:46,690
We've been planning this party
for such a long time.

527
00:19:46,770 --> 00:19:49,270
We had to make excuses for why
we couldn't attend Gummy's party

528
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:51,170
So that we could get
everything ready for yours.

529
00:19:51,530 --> 00:19:53,190
Twilight: if this is
a farewell party,

530
00:19:53,250 --> 00:19:55,550
Why does the cake I picked up
from sugar cube corner

531
00:19:55,630 --> 00:19:57,930
Say "happy birthday,
Pinkie Pie"?

532
00:20:06,930 --> 00:20:08,350
[ Whoosh! ]

533
00:20:08,410 --> 00:20:09,010
[ Squeak! ]

534
00:20:09,110 --> 00:20:11,030
Because it's my birthday!

535
00:20:11,210 --> 00:20:13,670
Oh, how could I have forgotten
my own birthday?

536
00:20:14,510 --> 00:20:15,870
[ All sigh ]

537
00:20:16,130 --> 00:20:17,010
[ Thud! ]

538
00:20:17,370 --> 00:20:18,330
And you like me so much,

539
00:20:18,390 --> 00:20:20,330
You decided to throw me
a surprise party!

540
00:20:21,250 --> 00:20:23,330
That's what we've been trying
to tell you, darling.

541
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:26,150
You girls are
the best friends ever!

542
00:20:27,710 --> 00:20:29,710
How could I have
ever doubted you?

543
00:20:30,290 --> 00:20:31,650
It's okay, Pinkie Pie.

544
00:20:31,770 --> 00:20:33,670
It could've happened
to any of us.

545
00:20:33,830 --> 00:20:35,270
[ Laughter ]

546
00:20:35,330 --> 00:20:36,390
Don't worry
about it.

547
00:20:36,650 --> 00:20:39,690
I'm just glad I haven't been
replaced by a bucket of turnips.

548
00:20:39,930 --> 00:20:42,190
Huh?
You don't want
to know.

549
00:20:42,430 --> 00:20:44,230
All right, girls.
Enough of this gabbin'.

550
00:20:44,430 --> 00:20:45,170
[ Record scratches ]

551
00:20:45,390 --> 00:20:46,850
Let's party!

552
00:20:46,990 --> 00:20:49,670
[ Dance music plays ]

553
00:20:49,770 --> 00:20:52,330
[ Laughter ]

554
00:20:52,930 --> 00:20:54,710
Twilight:
dear princess Celestia,

555
00:20:54,910 --> 00:20:57,870
I am writing to you from
the most delightful party.

556
00:20:57,990 --> 00:21:00,870
I am not only having a great
time with my friends

557
00:21:00,950 --> 00:21:02,730
But also was given
the opportunity

558
00:21:02,770 --> 00:21:04,910
To learn a valuable lesson
about friendship.

559
00:21:05,410 --> 00:21:07,650
Always expect the best
from your friends

560
00:21:07,730 --> 00:21:09,270
And never assume the worst.

561
00:21:09,650 --> 00:21:11,250
Rest assured that a good friend

562
00:21:11,290 --> 00:21:13,410
Always has your best interests
at heart.

563
00:21:13,710 --> 00:21:16,090
Your faithful student,
Twilight Sparkle.

564
00:21:16,290 --> 00:21:18,070
You girls wouldn't mind
if we celebrated

565
00:21:18,130 --> 00:21:19,990
Gummy's after-Birthday party,
too, would you?

566
00:21:20,110 --> 00:21:22,750
His party was cut short,
and he's pretty upset about it.

567
00:21:22,810 --> 00:21:24,350
Rainbow: oh, sure!
Rarity: oh, definitely.

568
00:21:24,410 --> 00:21:25,890
We must have a party.

569
00:21:25,990 --> 00:21:27,570
Let's have a party
for Gummy.

570
00:21:27,670 --> 00:21:28,950
[ Laughter ]

